After the war ended, Ewan's hunger for[N]
knowledge only grew. He continued his[N]
studies in magic, traveling far and wide[N]
to learn from the most experienced sages[N]
and scholars. With his boundless enthusiasm[N]
and curiosity, Ewan eventually became a[N]
renowned sage, his magical abilities[N]
rivaling even those of his master, Saleh.[N]
But no matter how far he traveled or how[N]
much he learned, he always remembered the[N]
Friends he made during the war, especially[N]
Myrrh. It was said that Ewan's most powerful[N]
spells were inspired by the wisdom Myrrh[N]
shared with him, and that Myrrh's heart, once[N]
burdened by loneliness, was forever warmed[N]
by the lighthearted mage who saw her as more[N]
than just a dragon, but as a cherished friend.[X]
